8. Service creation?

USERS > SVC > DEPLOYMENT > Replica Set > POD

Whenver pod goes down, it will be back with replica set configuration (auto healing), pod ip will be changed. 
Users can't access the application in the pod via Ip address instead they can access via svc (default.com.svc)
A. Load balancing - Load balance will handle the reqeust and response traffic flow from the users as equal. 
B. Service Discovery - Now user can access Service but how service will access pod with IP address? Instead of IP address they reach via label & selector info.
C. Expose to world - Cluster IP, Node Port, Load Balacning. 
If service type is cluster ip, then people who has access to only kubernetes cluster those can access the POD.
If it is node port, then who can access the application is deployed within the organization and access to services like ec2, vpc, s3 then they can access the pod.
If it is load balancing, then the user with the public ip can access the pod, If it is EKS then ELB will provide the public ip using C-C-M (cloud control manager) 
SVC will share the public ip to the users.

